6 (d) Whenever the department approves a request submitted under this section, the department:
7 (i) may authorize the alternative procurement method on a trial basis; and
8 (ii) if the alternative procurement method is employed, shall make a written determination as to the
9 success of the method.
10 (e) If the department determines that the alternative procurement method is successful and should
11 be an alternative that is generally available, it shall promulgate rules that establish the use of the alternative
12 procurement method as an additional source selection method. The rules promulgated by the department under
13 this subsection must reflect the purposes described in 18-4-122."
